doc.after: One of the most visible Hispanic legacies is the prevalence of Spanish names and surnames among Filipinos a Spanish name and surname however does not necessarily denote Spanish ancestry This peculiarity unique among the people of Asia came as a result of a colonial edict by Governor General Narciso Claver a y Zaldua which ordered the systematic distribution of family names and implementation of Hispanic nomenclature on the population 380
